Titre
Research Engineer or Postdoctoral Researcher in Remote Sensing and Precision Agriculture

Information sur l’Offre d’Emploi
Profile
The candidate should have a doctoral degree, or an engineer’s degree, or a master’s degree in remote sensing, or computer sciences, or data science, or another field that is closely linked to these;
Roles and Responsibilities
Working on data processing and programming to improve and automate variables and products extraction;
Developing remote sensing and precision agriculture-based products such as biomass, yield, soil moisture, evapotranspiration, crop classification, 3D canopy and terrain maps, etc.;
Organize data, code, clean up pipeline, and produce weekly reporting;
Build sample planning techniques, fertilization prescription maps, and 3D mapping;
Make suggestions for new paths of investigation that are connected to the goals of the project.
Required Skills and Experience
Strong background knowledge and expertise with geospatial image processing and GIS software applications (ArcGIS; QGIS ENVI; Pix4D; etc.);
Excellent knowledge of statistics as well as computer programming languages (R, Python, MATLAB, etc.);
Good experience in processing and analyzing remote sensing data is desired. A focus on LiDAR and multispectral data is required.
Good experience in remote sensing, GIS, and modelling for precision agricultural technologies;
Skills in scientific writing, publishing, and communication are strongly required;
The candidate should have at least two years of experience in remote sensing, data science, and/or precision agriculture.
Type of the contract:
CDD 12 MONTHS

