As a GIS Analyst, you will help the Team capture and analyze a range of geographical data using GIS systems to help our organization make long-term plans for our projects.
Company Overview & Position Description
Established in 2013, Lixia Capsia Gestionis (LixCap), is an international development consultancy founded by finance experts passionate about mobilizing private sector resources to achieve sustainable development outcomes. A U.S.-based company with roots in North Africa and offices in Casablanca, Morocco, Tunis, Tunisia, and Washington D.C, USA. LixCap’s mission is to support economic development in emerging markets. LixCap offers expertise that bridges the Anglophone and Francophone worlds, providing market insights and project support to government agencies, private sector companies and donor agencies such as USAID, USDA, USTDA, the World Bank Group, and the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development (EBRD). LixCap specializes in investment development, from advisory work to programming in entrepreneurship and private sector access, to finance development with a special emphasis on agribusiness, logistics, green economy investment, and renewable energy.
The LixCap team includes professionals that are skilled in investment fund structuring, econometric analyses, market assessments, financial modeling, debt and equity financing, cold chain, and third-party logistics. LixCap values staff members that are interested in professional development, innovation, and supporting the growth of our company into new sectors and geographies.
Responsibilities
§Work on projects, scoping out the nature and purpose of the information required;
Utilize multiple databases and GIS software to perform spatial analysis for any given project working with a team;
Conduct spatial analysis for site selection;
Collect, store, analyze, manipulate and present a range of complex geographical and spatial data and provide input/recommendations in order to support a variety of projects;
Produce, update, and maintain cartographic outputs and graphic files;
Use tools to join together different GIS datasets and create new information or investigate patterns;
Use a range of satellite images tools to analyze and describe any given geographical object;
Georeferencing and digitizing to convert paper maps to GIS datasets;
Create and edit geospatial data, using GPS and digitizing techniques; create and edit maps, integrating a range of data formats;
Produce a wide variety of reports and maps, prepare data, analysis, maps, and mapping applications for various Projects;
Perform a variety of technical tasks relative to the assigned area of responsibility.
Minimum Requirements:
Education: Master’s degree in Geographic Information System (GIS) or closely related field, or equivalent experience. Certifications would be a plus;
Experience: Minimum 2 years of work experience in the same field;
Solid grasp of ArcGIS desktop tools: ArcPro, ArcMap, ArcCatalog, ArcView, ArcEditor, ArcInfo, etc;
Ability to address multiple tasks simultaneously;
Ability to handle changing and emerging priorities. Knowledge of utility distribution systems;
Good analytical skills, ability to quantify data, and make sound decisions;
Ability to organize, plan and work efficiently within a highly technical environment;
Strong written and verbal communication skills in French & English.
Preferred Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities:
Understanding of Integrated GPS and GIS principles;
ESRI ArcGIS products;
ESRI Certificate;
Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, Outlook, PowerPoint, etc.);
Design software (Photoshop, Illustrator);
Ability to independently research and learn new skills and processes;
Ability to effectively communicate in a cross-cultural and cross-functional environment;
Excellent interpersonal communication skills;
Fluency in English & French, proficiency in Spanish is highly advantageous;
Technology focused.
Benefits:
Flexible working hours;
Growth opportunities inside the company for high-performing and motivated team members.
